      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. so if the shrinkage is a lot higher than we thought, it's basically making our COGS look better than it actually is? and how much does a 5% increase in shrinkage actually tank the turnover ratio if our average inventory is around $2M? can you run a quick example for me?",
