      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Not quite; higher shrinkage makes your COGS **look worse** than it actually is, because you are failing to account for the missing goods in your recorded costs. If your shrinkage increases by 5% and your average inventory is $2M, you need the baseline COGS to give an exact number, but generally, this unrecorded loss will significantly depress your turnover ratio. For instance, if your original COGS was $10M, adding a 5% shrinkage loss ($500k) would increase COGS to $10.5M, dropping your ratio from 5x to about 4.76x.",
