      "content": "When footage is silent, the investigation often shifts to internal process failures rather than external theft. You should first scrutinize receiving and stocking procedures for potential overages or miscounts during intake. Next, review picking and packing logs to see if errors are occurring before the item leaves the warehouse floor. Finally, conduct cycle counts on the high-value bins specifically, as systematic administrative errors are a common source of \"phantom\" shrinkage.",
